org.pikater.web.experiment.client

Class ExperimentGraphClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pikater.web.experiment.client.ExperimentGraphClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<BoxInfoClient>, IExperimentGraph<java.lang.Integer,BoxInfoClient>

    public class ExperimentGraphClient
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, IExperimentGraph<java.lang.Integer,BoxInfoClient>
    A special (GWT&Vaadin)-compliant experiment graph implementation. As such, fields are required to be public and a public default constructor is needed. This class is only used to efficiently transport already defined experiments to the client. All experiments in experiment editor are actually stored on the server.
    Author:
    SkyCrawl
